en China and Europe, and analyzes the China Dream that drives much of current Chinese foreign policy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aGreat powersxPhilosophy. 0aImperialismxPhilosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aHistory : History. 4aPolitics and Law : International Relations. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846750440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438467504423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438467504/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles